Date: 0/0/1988
Source: Lexicographical & Linguistic Studies
Author:
Vol / Page: 189
Edition:
Quote: Aiga /a:|ina/. Also ainga. [Samoan `aiga.] A (Samoan) family. Also attrib. Used to denote a nuclear family (father, mother, and children) or an extended one. In Samoan there are alsoother senses: lineage; kin, relatives; home; consummation (of marriage). See G.B. Milner Samoan Dictionary (1966) s.v.
Notes: Burchfield

